<HL>
   Business Brief -- MCI Communications Corp.:
   Purchase of Telecom USA
   Is Approved by the FCC
</HL>
<DATE>
08/01/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   MCIC TTT
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL COMMUNICATIONS COMMISSION (FCC)
</GV>
<LP>
   The Federal Communications Commission approved MCI
Communications Corp.'s planned acquisition of Telecom USA
Inc., Atlanta.
   The agency's Common Carrier Bureau found that the
combination "would continue to be subject to vigorous
competition" from American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co., United
Telecommunications' Sprint Communications Corp. unit and
other long-distance carriers. MCI is the U.S.'s second
largest long-distance company, and Telecom USA is the fourth
largest.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   An MCI spokeswoman said the company expects to complete
the $1.25 billion merger this month after receiving approval
from various state regulators.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
