</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP HAN
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   PowerGen PLC reported pretax profit of #233.6 million
($431.6 million) for the year ended March 31. The company is
one of two U.K. electricity generating companies scheduled to
be privatized in February.
   The results, made public for the first time, also showed a
