   Comparative figures for the year earlier weren't provided.
   Robert Malpas, PowerGen chairman, wouldn't comment on a
possible bid for the company by Hanson PLC, a British
industrial conglomerate, which the government has said might
pre-empt a public share sale.
   Mr. Malpas also wouldn't comment on speculation that
PowerGen management might launch its own bid for control of
the company.
</TEXT>
