   Eagle also said Ernest J. Torrizo, a director of the First
Federal Savings Bank unit, and Steven E. Lasewics Jr., a
director of the Bristol Federal Savings unit, were named
directors of the parent company, increasing the board
membership to 10.
   The boards for the subsidiaries have been replaced by the
Eagle board, which will serve concurrently as the board for
the subsidiaries, the company said. The reorganization
reduces the total number of directors to 10 from 19.
